name: Cookshop Food Services
product_desc:
Cookshop is an ecosystem that links local growers/producers, food retailers, and advertisers directly to consumers.
	* Our online food delivery service aggregates the menus of local food retailers in an easy to use interface for tech savvy consumers.
	* Our produce distribution service uses harvest tracking to create a virtual marketplace for local growers who typically lack access to markets.
	* Our online grocery delivery service brings local produce to high value consumers and food retailers.
	* Our platform allows advertisers to target consumers through various methods including, SMS messaging, online advertising, and flier distribution.
	* Our  digital finance network connects all parties in our ecosystem, bringing developing markets into the digital economy on a level playing field.
	* Lastly, for every 10 orders we receive through Cookshop, we donate a free meal to school-aged child who needs it.

name: LuckyLoo
product_desc:
LuckyLoo will be the FIRST and only public toilet operator in Liberia, utilizing the collected waste to produce organic fertilizer (a critical element of Liberian President Ellen Johnson Sirleaf's largest initiative: local agriculture), and eventually, the Country's first Waste2Energy treatment center.

Public defecation is a major issue in Liberia's capital city, and is becoming a growing health concern. Personal toilets, or latrines, are too expensive for the urban poor to build and maintain, so most people simply opt for the public streets.

At one point in West Point, one of the worst slums in the world, there were fewer than 10 public, non-maintained, bathrooms for a population of more than 60,000.

LuckyLoo looks to offer sanitary and dignified options to the people of Monrovia.

product_desc: The Olivia S. Washington School's of  Liberia are  non profit institutions dedicated to serving the educational needs of children from Gbarngba Town to Monrovia Liberia and environs.
